Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and 4 tsp @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Add @shredded carrots{4%ounce} and toss to coat. Set aside.

Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces; place in a #large pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; rub with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Reserve ¼ tsp @smoky cinnamon paprika spice{1%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{} for the next step; rub pork all over with remaining Cinnamon Paprika Spice.

Place pork on a #baking sheet{} and roast on middle rack until cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

> Swap in chicken for pork; roast 15-20 minutes.

While pork roasts, quarter, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}; add to #bowl{} with carrots and toss to combine. Stir in half the scallion greens and season with salt and pepper.

To bowl with reserved Cinnamon Paprika Spice, add @cherry jam{2} and remaining vinegar; stir to combine. Microwave until warm, ~{30-60%seconds}. Stir in @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Mash drained potatoes until smooth; stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and remaining scallion greens. If needed, add reserved potato cooking liquid a splash at a time until potatoes are creamy. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork, potatoes, and slaw between plates. Drizzle sauce over pork and serve.